1. Every new function must have a complete Google-style docstring.

2. Every new module must have a module-level docstring explaining its purpose
   and which pipeline layer it belongs to.

3. Type hints are required on every function signature.

4. All new constants must be defined at module level (not inside functions).

5. No function should be longer than 60 lines. Decompose if needed.

6. All tests must use pytest. No unittest.TestCase. Parametrize where
   the same assertion applies to multiple input/output pairs.

7. Tests must not require OPENAI_API_KEY. Mock the OpenAI client using
   pytest-mock or unittest.mock wherever LLM calls are involved.

8. After implementing all sections, run a final check:
   - Do any existing tests in tests/ now fail? Fix them.
   - Does `PYTHONPATH=src pytest tests/ -q` complete without errors?
   - Does the import graph have any circular imports? Resolve if so.

9. Do not change the result dict schema. The existing fields must remain;
   you may add new fields but not remove or rename existing ones.

10. Preserve existing behaviour for all languages already in the pipeline
    (ar, ru, uk, el, ja, zh). The changes in Sections 1, 6, 7, 11 modify
    these languages — ensure backward compatibility by verifying existing
    golden-dataset cases still pass after each section is implemented.